ransfer spinach-egg mixture onto lined Varoma tray, spread to the borders, sprinkle with reserved grated cheese and insert Varoma tray into Varoma dish."},{"content":"Place onions, carrots, remaining 30 g olive oil, tomatoes, |1-2 basil leaves, water, stock paste and ½ tsp salt into mixing bowl and chop <b>5 sec\/speed 5<b>."},{"content":"Insert simmering basket and add mixed vegetables into it. Place Varoma into position, secure Varoma lid and cook <b>30 min\/Varoma\/speed 1<b>. Remove Varoma. With aid of baking paper lining, roll up the spinach omelette, keeping it wrapped in the baking paper. Meanwhile remove simmering basket with aid of spatula, transfer cooked vegetables to a shallow serving dish, season with salt to taste and stir. Unwrap the spinach omelette and cut in slices (approx. 2 cm). Transfer slices to serving dish with vegetables and keep warm. Transfer tomato soup to a serving bowl, add reserved steamed garlic bread to the soup, drizzle with some extra virgin olive oil and garnish with torn basil leaves. Serve the soup hot as a starter and the rolled omelette warm as a main dish with the ratatouille vegetables on the side."}],"hintsAndTricks":["For a smooth soup, after removing Varoma and simmering basket in <b>step 6,<b> blend <b><b>1 min\/speed 5-10,<b><b> <b>increasing speed gradually from speed 5 to speed 10.<b> Add the steamed garlic bread and serve as described in <b>step 6.<b>","To make your own bread, refer to recipes in <i>The Basic Cookbook<\/i>.","Replace spinach in the rolled omelette with vegetables of your choice (e.g. cabbage, zucchini)."],"basicInfo":["medium","35m","1h 5m","4 portions"]}